Market Analysis and Insights
Global Commercial Refrigerator and Freezer Market
The commercial refrigerator and freezer market is projected to grow at a rate of 7.00% from 2022 to 2029. A report by Data Bridge Market Research offers insights into the key factors influencing this growth and their impact on the market during the forecast period. The rise in urbanization is a major driver of market expansion.
Commercial refrigeration refers to the process of removing excess heat from a source or material to maintain a temperature lower than the surrounding environment. Commercial refrigerators and freezers are used to preserve food items such as fruits, vegetables, meat, and more.
The global demand for frozen and processed food is a key driver of the commercial refrigerator and freezer market. Market growth is further accelerated by the expansion of the tourism and hospitality sector, increased international food trade, and rising demand for frozen food refrigeration. Factors such as the growing preference for takeaway meals, advancements in technologies like ammonia absorption systems and liquid-vapor compression, rising disposable incomes, increased food expenditure, lifestyle changes, and health-conscious consumers positively impact the market. Additionally, the need for efficient control and monitoring of commercial kitchen environments offers lucrative opportunities for market players from 2022 to 2029.
